			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Summoning really isn't the issue for specialization.  I generally summon my food, water, bandages, weps, pet, etc once when I log on. At level 23 it takes about 1/2 bar of mana.  I med and am ready to go.  Specializing in conj at this point saves a few minutes of time.  I also solo a lot and find that my pet doesn't usually kill a mob all by itself.  Also if it does, I lose 1/2 the exp and gain exp slower.  So at some point you have to burn or heal.  I do both, but I like the advantage that spec in evo has when you need or want to burn. I acknowledge that some of the dd spells are conj, but most (including the most powerful later in the game) are evo. I feel that spec evo helps out more when you need it (during combat) vs your martha white stage when you are summoning and can spend a few extra minutes medding before you start.  Many people spec in conj and many in evo, both have advantages.
				</font>
			</td>

